1970-01-01 00:10:00 1. Mix all purpose flour and water in 1:1 ratio in a bowl and add in the eggs and dashi stock powder.

2. Add in the salt and sugar and give it a good mix until combined

3. Thinly slice the cabbage and green onions and mix it into the batter

4. Add oil to the pan and scoop mix into the pan when the pan is hot

5. Flip over when golden brown

6. Add the thinly sliced pork on top of the pancake and cook until brown

7. Add okonomiyaki sauce on top along with Japanese mayo
